str.format() => { Variable Substitution , Value Formatting }

Example:
 Single Placeholder ... print( "Sammy has {} balloons.".format(5) )
 Multiple Placeholders ... 
   sammy_string = "Sammy loves {} {}, and has {} {}."
   print( sammy_string.format("open_source", "software", 5, "balloons"))

 Positional Arguments ...
   sammy_string = "sammy is a {3}, {2} and {1} {0}!"
   print( sammy_string.format("happy", "smiling", "blue", "shark") )

   Sammy is a shark, blue and smiling happy !

Keyword arguments ...
   sammy_string = "Sammy the {0} {1} a {pr}."
   print( sammy_string.format("shark", "made", pr = "pull request") )
   
   Sammy the shark made a pull request

Type Specification ...
   {field_name:conversion}

   Format Specification Mini-Language
    '<' ... Left-aligned field
    '>' ... Right-aligned field
    '=' ... Padding is placed
    's' ... String format
    'b' ... Binary
    'c' ... Character
    'd' ... Decimal
    'o' ... Octal
    'x' ... Hex 

